This interposition of Samaria between Galilee and -Jndea must be remembered, when we read the borders and portions of the tribes set out, Ezek. xlviii3 where Manasseh and Ephraim (the country of Samaria) are bounded and set out as formerly, but must not be reckoned under the notion of Samaria, as they had been.
